President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of South Carolina due to the effects of Hurricane Florence. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency protective measures and hazard mitigation measures in certain counties. Elizabeth Turner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and more counties and forms of assistance may be designated in the future. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.